commitResults.messageTitle: Add SessionDuration class and DefaultDuration enum
commitResults.messageBody:
SessionDuration class:
The SessionDuration class wraps a java.time Duration object and allows common time operations to be executed on the duration object

DefaultDuration enum:
This enum defines some preset durations that can be used

commitResults.messageTitle: Change toString method for DefaultDuration enum to output in a more user-friendly format
Move SessionDuration and DefaultDuration to its own package for ease of categorization
Refactor SessionDuration to track for information
commitResults.messageBody:
SessionDuration is a class that tracks the duration of the session
The class should cover all scenarios such as breaks and study since they can still be thought of as a session

Included new attributes such as durationLeft and durationPassed to keep track of how much time is left and how much time has passed
Refactored duration attribute to a private final object as that can be referenced to reset the duration

commitResults.messageTitle: Change reduceTimeFromTimer and addTimeToTimer to take in milliseconds instead of seconds

commitResults.messageBody:
Main Implementation:
1. Convert all time references to a SessionDuration object to encapsulate all the data
2. Convert the List of breakDurations to store a List of SessionDuration objects instead of long datatypes
3. Refactor getTotalBreakTime to get the number of seconds used for the break

Main Implementations:
1. Change constructor to take in a SessionDuration object
This is because the TimerManager manages the duration left in each object, and it makes sense that it takes in a SessionDuration object to manage

2. Create REFRESH_PERIOD static reference to remove magic numbers

3. Modify start method such that time reduced is the REFRESH_PERIOD instead of elapsed time
This is because the actual number of milliseconds passed is not exactly 1000 everytime. Thus, it causes some display issues when displaying the time left since 1 second might not be subtracted each time

4. Modify pause method to use the SessionDuration object

5. Modify resume method to use the SessionDuration object. Changes for resume method is similar to the changes for start method
